# App Boundary Rule

This repository owns the Haderach homepage SPA and the shared UI design system (@haderach/shared-ui). It is integrated into the external platform control plane.

- Keep strict separation of concerns:
  - This repo owns the homepage app, shared UI components, CI patterns, and artifact publish contracts.
  - Platform orchestration, promotion, and cross-app routing checks remain outside this repo.
- Keep app logic and app tests in this repository; do not add platform orchestration logic here.
- Keep naming kebab-case for repo/path conventions unless language-specific rules require otherwise.
- Prefer explicit docs and small config contracts over heavy scripts or premature automation.
- Use or update docs when behavior/contracts change:
  - `README.md`
  - `docs/architecture.md`
- Preserve security/indexing defaults:
  - default `noindex` / `nofollow`
  - only allow indexing with explicit approval path documented
- When adding new structure, keep it minimal and production-minded.
- Follow task lifecycle and formatting rules defined in:
  - `.cursor/rules/todo-conventions.mdc`

## Dev Server Hygiene

Before starting a local dev server, kill any existing Vite/Node dev servers across all workspace repos to avoid port conflicts and stale processes:

```sh
lsof -iTCP:5173 -iTCP:5174 -iTCP:5175 -iTCP:5176 -sTCP:LISTEN -t 2>/dev/null | xargs kill 2>/dev/null
```

Always kill dev servers when finishing a session or switching tasks.
